result.name: Tong Tong Town

reviews.text:
Exceptional services here, the waitress here are always smiling and with lots of patience.

The prices of the foods here are probably towards the higher side, but it’s worth it. The taste of the food are just right, must try the almond pig lungs soup, really delicious. 

Would come back here :)
really good food - some dishes are similar to other popular contemporary dim sum places, but they do their own take on it and the result is quite surprisingly delectable!

If you order their grilled chicken and ask the restaurant to serve in portions between friends, the restaurant will charge you hkd 30 for such service.... Interesting charges..... 切雞費……… 

If you come with friends, welcome to try the barbarian way, just remember don't order this dish in business occasions.
Expensive Cantonese food, fried noodles for $79!! overall fun atmosphere, good food good vibes. The food doesn't stand out particularly, it's good though! Would return but definitely pricey.
New style yam cha com Chinese restaurant, quite rare yet nice dishes available.  It may not suit everyone but well recommended for at least a trial.  All food are well prepared.

reviews.text:

Would come back here :)

食物得相樣，好睇唔好食。
茶位：$9（無茶揀）
鮑汁花膠撈粗（$98）-麵好硬，個汁味道似蒸的豉油，好咸。
蝦子扣柚皮（$69）-無咩味
黑金流沙包（$49）-唔太流心，味道尚可
4代仝堂糕（$55）-扭麻花唔脆又硬，砵仔糕又甜又粉，另外兩樣ok
八味脆豆腐（$55）-唔錯，外脆内滑，食得出新鮮炸起。
好失望，食物價錢同地段，賣相成正比，但同味道無咩關係。
